{"questionId":"21457","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>An engineer plans to visit six oil rigs <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>(</mo><mtext>A</mtext><mo>–</mo><mtext>F</mtext><mo>)</mo></math> in the Gulf of Mexico, starting and finishing at <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>A</mtext></math>.&nbsp;The travelling time, in minutes, between each of the rigs is shown in the table.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\"><img src=\"__IMG__/e74b8f28f79da5ed56d1270e0780cee602a6c90f.png\"></p>\n<p>The data above can be represented by a graph <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>G</mi></math>.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Hence find a lower bound for the travelling time needed to visit all the oil rigs.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>AB</mtext><mo>+</mo><mtext>AC</mtext><mo>=</mo><mn>55</mn><mo>+</mo><mn>63</mn><mo>=</mo><mn>118</mn></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>174</mn><mo>+</mo><mn>118</mn><mo>=</mo><mn>292</mn></math>&nbsp;minutes&nbsp;&nbsp; <em><strong>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; A1</strong></em>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><em><strong><br>[2 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"21457","referenceCode":"21M.1.AHL.TZ1.10a.ii","subjectId":"51-dp-mathematics-applications-and-interpretation","title":"Hence find a lower bound for the travelling time needed to visit all the oil rigs.","paper":"1","level":"HL","questionNumber":"a.ii","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 2]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 3—Geometry and trigonometry","Topic 3—Geometry and trigonometry","AHL 3.16—Tree and cycle algorithms, Chinese postman, travelling salesman"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}